remixlab.bias.event

Class MotionShortcut

  • java.lang.Object
    • remixlab.bias.Shortcut
      • remixlab.bias.event.MotionShortcut

  • public final class MotionShortcut
extends Shortcut
    This class represents MotionEvent shortcuts.

    Motion shortcuts can be of one of two forms: 1. A gesture-id (e.g., 'LEFT_ID' , or even 'NO_ID') or, ; 2. A gesture-id + modifier key combinations (e.g., 'RIGHT_ID' + 'CTRL').

    Note that the shortcut may be empty: the no-id (NO_ID) and no-modifier-mask (NO_MODIFIER_MASK) combo may also defined a shortcut. Empty shortcuts may bind gesture-less motion interactions (e.g., mouse move without any button pressed).

    Note that the motion-event Shortcut.id() DOFs should be registered first (see registerID(int, String)) before using the shortcut.

      • defaultEventClass

        public Class<? extends MotionEvent> defaultEventClass()
        Description copied from class: Shortcut
        Returns the default-event class (alternative to Shortcut.eventClass()) this shortcut is to be attached to. Default value is null.

        Override it when an optional Shortcut.eventClass() is needed (rarely). For an example refer to the MotionEvent implementation.

        See Also:
        Shortcut.eventClass()
